description:
r/Talesfromtechsupport In today's video, OP works as an IT tech and he's faced with an interesting mystery. For some reason, a printer keeps malfunctioning whenever the secretary uses it. Everyone else can use the printer just fine, but the secretary keeps breaking the printer. OP shows up to test things out, and he eventually solves the mystery. It turns out that the secretary kept accidentally pressing buttons... but not with her hands! If you like this podcast, follow my podcast for more daily Reddit content!
